    "narrative": "The Austin Waves' offensive engine is centered today around **Gunnar Henderson**, whose matchup against Houser produces an elite score of 81.88. Benefiting from a substantial 16% park factor boost and a favorable platoon dynamic, **Gunnar Henderson** is the clear anchor of the lineup. **Marcell Ozuna** and **Miguel Vargas** also offer high-floor production; **Marcell Ozuna** is buoyed by a 10% wind-out factor against Taillon, while **Miguel Vargas** takes advantage of the lead-off spot and favorable atmospheric conditions to reach a strong 64.07 score. Even facing the formidable deGrom, **Kyle Tucker** remains a recommended start (60.76), as the wind-out conditions and his high-end xwOBA mitigate the risk of the elite opposing arm.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was **Josh Jung**, who landed at 57.90\u2014just missing the cut. Despite facing Sasaki and his lofty 5.52 xERA, **Josh Jung** was squeezed out primarily due to his lower batting order position, which caps his run and RBI upside compared to the starters. We are also monitoring **Andy Pages** (50.01) closely; while he is in the lineup, his proximity to the marginal tier reflects the difficulty of attacking deGrom, though his role as a base-stealing threat makes him an essential hold given our scarcity-focused strategy. We remain cautious with **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, whose 53.67 score is dragged down by a significant 19% penalty against the skilled Woodruff, though he is currently our best available option at the MI spot.",
